gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Level 3 Ecoregions for the Susquehanna River Basin: Pennsylvania, 2006

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: Polygon shapefile that depicts level 3 ecoregions for the Susquehanna River Basin (2006 boundary). Ecoregions are based on perceived patterns of a combination of causal and integrative factors including land use, land surface form, potential natural vegetation, and soils (Omernik, 1987). This is a copy of the ecoregion coverage of Omernik (1987) with some item names modified.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: Dataset developed to fit the needs of the Susquehanna River Basin Commission and is intended for educational display purposes only.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: The coverage was installed from an ARC/INFO EXPORT file supplied by EPA Corvallis. Some item names were modified and others were redefined to make the coverage more convenient to use and to conform to more conventional item names.
Rev. 1.1 Converted to Data General workstation. Item redefinitions revised and documentation added.

Downloaded the .e00 file for aquatic ecoregions for the U.S. from the USGS. The file was imported to ArcView 3.2 and converted to a shapefile. The shapefile was reprojected from PROJECTION ALBERS UNITS METERS SPHEROID CLARKE1866 XSHIFT 0 YSHIFT 0 PARAMETERS 29 30 00 45 30 00 -96 00 00 23 00 00 0.0 0.0 to Geographic or unprojected. The shapefile was clipped to the Susquehanna River Basin extent using hy_wshed_susquehanna.shp.

Due to changes in the Susquehanna River Basin boundary, this file had to be re-clipped to the 2006 version of the basin boundary. The coverage "ecorgns" was found on disk 418 of the SRBC library. This coverage was reprojected to SRBC projection (NAD83 Albers Equal Area Conic) and called ecoregion_repro.shp. It was brought into ArcMap and verified as the base layer for the original SRBC ecoregion.shp dataset. Ecoregion_repro.shp was then clipped to the 2006 version of the Basin boundary.
US dataset of ecoregions used to clip to the basin.
